<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,320]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,186,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">Note.</emphasis>
Børge Petersen (unpublished) labelled the specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Radoszkowski, 1879" authorityName="Radoszkowski" authorityYear="1879" box="[917,1347,186,212]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binotata">
<emphasis box="[917,1102,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">Mutilla binotata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Radoszkowski, O." box="[1111,1347,186,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77" pagination="140 - 156" refId="ref19754" refString="Radoszkowski, O. (1879) Les Chrysides et Sphegides du Caucase. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae, 15 (2 - 3), 140 - 156." type="journal article" year="1879">Radoszkowski, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Radoszkowski, 1890" authorityName="Radoszkowski" authorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="araratica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">M. araratica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Radoszkowski, O." box="[266,501,222,248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77" pagination="502 - 510" refId="ref19863" refString="Radoszkowski, O. (1890) Hymenopteres recoltes sur le mont Ararat. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae, 24 (3 - 4), 502 - 510." type="journal article" year="1890">
Radoszkowski, 
<quantity box="[445,501,222,248]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8006" pageId="16" pageNumber="77" unit="in" value="1890.0">1890</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in MNHU with Radoszkowski’s “Type” labels as the 
<typeStatus box="[1122,1239,222,248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">lectotypes</typeStatus>
. Since no validly published 
<typeStatus box="[267,381,258,284]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">lectotypes</typeStatus>
designation has yet been made, we hereby designate the specimens so labelled by Petersen as the 
<typeStatus box="[192,298,294,320]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">lectotype</typeStatus>
